\section{Introduction}

 \begin{frame}{Context and code presentation}
    Many articles have been published from wolf reintroduction in \textbf{Yellowstone National Park} (YNP) until now, talking about vegetation recovery after their reintroduction (Beschta and Ripple, 2016), but also about land cover changes in this area in the last years (Potter, 2019). \\
    Other sources, like the official \href{https://www.globalforestwatch.org/}{global forest watch website}, report a forest cover loss during the years from 2001 to 2021, showing a decrease in it. \\
    With my code I wanted to check this changes in land cover, with special regard to vegetation, in the area of Yellowstone National Park from wolf reintroduction, on 12th January 1995, until now, 2022.
    
 \end{frame}

\section{Images sources and searching criteria}

 \subsection{Image sources}
   \begin{frame}{Image source: USGS website}
    The years I selected for the analysis are 1995, 2015 and 2022. The images of of 2015 and 2022 come from Landsat 8-9 OLI/TIRS, while images of 1995 come from Landsat 4-5 TM, both from landsat 2 - collection 2. The source of the images is USGS EarthExplorer website.
   \end{frame}

 \subsection{Searching Criteria}
   \begin{frame}{Searching Criteria}
    Searching criteria started from determining the coordinates of the study area (Figure \ref{Fig:1}).
